1995年，該學院曾經拒絕參加《[[美國新聞和世界報道|美國新聞和世界報道]]》的大學排名，是第一個拒絕參加該排名的大學，原因是1994年《[[華爾街日報|華爾街日報]]》爆料稱有大學偽造數據以提高各自的排名<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reed.edu/apply/college-rankings.html|title=Reed College {{!}} Admission {{!}} Reed College Admission Office|website=www.reed.edu|access-date=2016-03-02|archive-date=2021-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506033515/https://www.reed.edu/apply/college-rankings.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，然而《美國新聞和世界報道》並未將其除名。<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1601839,00.html|newspaper=Time|date=March 21, 2001|last=Rawe|first=Julie|title=The College Rankings Revolt|accessdate=2018-04-08|archive-date=2007-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071123153415/http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1601839,00.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

該學院的師生比為1:9<ref name="ratio">{{cite web|url=https://www.reed.edu/ir/stufacratio.html|title=Reed College Student/Faculty Ratio|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Reed College|accessdate=July 9, 2017|archive-date=2020-10-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201010093415/https://www.reed.edu/ir/stufacratio.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。錄取率在30%左右<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.reed.edu/reed_magazine/sallyportal/posts/2016/reed-welcomes-class-of-2020.html |title=Adventure Begins for the Class of 2020 |publisher=Reed College |accessdate=August 24, 2016 |archive-date=2020-12-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210172110/https://www.reed.edu/reed_magazine/sallyportal/posts/2016/reed-welcomes-class-of-2020.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。作為美國最貴的學院之一，2018/19年學費高達70,550美元<ref name="ReferenceA">{{cite web|last1=College|first1=Reed|title=Reed College {{!}} Admission {{!}} Costs & Financial Aid|url=http://www.reed.edu/apply/costs.html|website=www.reed.edu|accessdate=14 April 2018|language=en-us|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226090708/https://www.reed.edu/apply/costs.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 声誉==

===毒品===
自1960年代以來，里德學院就因縱容學生吸食藥物而知名<ref>{{cite news | title = Rogue of the Week | work = Willamette Week | date = April 24, 2002 | url = http://www.wweek.com/portland/article-955-the_federal_bureau_of_investigation.html | accessdate = 2018-10-04 | archive-date = 2016-03-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160304070341/http://www.wweek.com/portland/article-955-the_federal_bureau_of_investigation.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>。《[[大学入学内部指南|大学入学内部指南]]》報道：“據學生們說，除非已經有學生遭到傷害或被騷擾，該學校不會用與藥物或酒有關的原因開除學生”。<ref name="yaledaily">{{cite book |title=The Insider's Guide to the Colleges, 2006 |author=''[[Yale_Daily_News|Yale Daily News]]'' staff |edition=32nd |date=July 16, 2005 |publisher=[[St._Martin's_Press|St. Martin's Press]] |location=New York |isbn= 0-312-34157-1 |page=771}}</ref>

2008年4月，一名名叫艾利克斯·路迟（Alex Lluch）的學生因在學校宿舍內吸食海洛因過量死亡<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/news/oregonian/index.ssf?/base/news/1207621554181530.xml&coll=7|title=Death on campus stuns Reed|last=Bernstein|first=Maxine|date=April 8, 2008|accessdate=September 22, 2008|work=The Oregonian|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304210234/http://www.oregonlive.com/news/oregonian/index.ssf?%2Fbase%2Fnews%2F1207621554181530.xml&coll=7|dead-url=no}}</ref>，由此牽連出許多類似的舊案<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/news/oregonian/susan_nielsen/index.ssf?/base/editorial/120796171467460.xml&coll=7|title=Drugs on Campus|last=Nielsen|first=Susan|date=April 13, 2008|work=The Oregonian|accessdate=September 22, 2008|archive-date=2013-12-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214092955/http://www.oregonlive.com/news/oregonian/susan_nielsen/index.ssf?%2Fbase%2Feditorial%2F120796171467460.xml&coll=7|dead-url=no}}</ref>。校長科林·戴弗（Colin Diver）表示他不清楚路迟事件屬於個例還是冰山一角，但他又說：“當人們談及里德的時候，總有兩個詞會出現在他們的腦海中，一個是頭腦，一個是毒品”<ref>{{cite news|last=Pitkin|first=James|url=http://www.wweek.com/portland/article-9009-higher_ed.html|title=Higher Ed|date=May 14, 2008|newspaper=[[Willamette_Week|Willamette Week]]|accessdate=January 2, 2013|archive-date=2016-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160809085422/http://www.wweek.com/portland/article-9009-higher_ed.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《[[维拉麦特周报|维拉麦特周报]]》的記者表示：“里德學院，作為全美學術聲譽最高的私立學校的一份子，是僅存的幾所給予學生幾乎無限度的吸毒自由的學校之一，而且政府部門還視之不見”。<ref>{{cite news|title=Inbox|date=May 21, 2008|newspaper=Willamette Week|url=http://www.wweek.com/portland/article-9031-inbox.html|accessdate=January 2, 2013|archive-date=2019-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011220535/https://www.wweek.com/portland/article-9031-inbox.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

同樣的事件再度發生於2010年3月<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.oregonlive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/03/reed_college_rattled_by_second.html | work=The Oregonian | title=Reed College rattled by second student death this month | date=March 23, 2010 | accessdate=2018-10-04 | archive-date=2018-11-06 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181106193305/https://www.oregonlive.com/news/index.ssf/2010/03/reed_college_rattled_by_second.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，當局這才決定進行干涉<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/27/education/27reed.html|title=Reed College’s President Is Told to Crack Down on Campus Drug Use|work=The New York Times|date=April 27, 2010|accessdate=July 29, 2013|archive-date=2021-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210424075309/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/27/education/27reed.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>[http://www.newsweek.com/2010/05/04/college-threatened-with-crack-house-law.html "College Threatened With ‘Crack House’ Law"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.newsweek.com/2010/05/04/college-threatened-with-crack-house-law.html |date=20160304211020 }}, ''[[Newsweek|Newsweek]]'', May 4, 2010]</ref>。2012年2月，里德學院報警稱“學生宿舍裡有兩個大三學生”擁有兩至三磅大麻和一些少量LSD等致幻劑<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/portland/index.ssf/2012/02/arrest_of_reed_students_on_mar.html|title=Arrest of Reed students on marijuana charges stirs campus debate|work=OregonLive.com|access-date=2018-04-14|language=en-US|archive-date=2018-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005071748/https://www.oregonlive.com/portland/index.ssf/2012/02/arrest_of_reed_students_on_mar.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在經過校內辯論之後，校長科林·戴弗向全體學生及教員發出公開信，稱學院再也不會容忍吸毒的行為了<ref name=":1" />。
